'''''Golan Front''''' is a 1985 video game published by [[Simulations Canada]].

==Gameplay==
''Golan Front'' is a [[computer wargame]] in which the battle fought by Israel against Egypt, Syria, Iraq, and Jordan in the [[Golan Heights]] is simulated.<ref name="CGW24"/> It features elements of [[board wargame|board wargaming]], such as [[Counter (board wargames)|counters]] and a physical map, in addition to computer play.<ref name=microcomputers />

==Reception==
William H. Harrington reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "''GF'' is a first rate military simulation."<ref name="CGW24">{{cite magazine |last=Harrington |first=William H. |title=Golan Front |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=Nov–Dec 1985 |volume=1 |issue=23 |pages=48–49}}</ref> ''[[Commodore Microcomputers]]'' named it one of the top computer wargames of 1986.<ref name=microcomputers>{{cite journal | title=The Best of 1986; The Best of War Games | author=Seiken, Jeff | date=November–December 1986 | journal=[[Commodore Microcomputers]] | number=6 | volume=7 | page=131 }}</ref>

